<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="65" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1437,1036,2030]" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,311,1868,1892]" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">Remarks:</emphasis>
The new species can be easily distinguished from 
<emphasis box="[849,927,1869,1892]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">P. v i rg o</emphasis>
by the adult facies (
<figureCitation box="[1145,1271,1869,1892]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1179,1200]" captionTargetBox="[171,1432,191,1103]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,191,1157]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Adults. 1. Platychasma elegantula sp. nov. Holotype, Guangxi, China, 21 July 2007, leg. L. Chen; 2. Platychasma elegantula sp. nov. Paratype, Guangxi, China, 4 May 2007, leg. L. Chen; 3. Platychasma virgo Butler, Honshu, Japan, 3 May 2004, leg. M. Owada; 4. Cyphanta xanthochlora Walker, Yunnan, China, 21 July 2006, leg. M. Wang and X. Fan." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/274411/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">
Figs. 
<number box="[1205,1246,1869,1892]" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" value="1.2">1, 2</number>
, 
<number box="[1257,1271,1869,1892]" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
), with a forewing costa that is straight and lacking basal swelling, and a median fascia of yellow to brown. The male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Platychasma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elegantula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">P. elegantula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are similar to those of 
<emphasis box="[483,561,1938,1961]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">P. v i rg o</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[580,684,1938,1961]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 7" captionStartId="1.[151,257,1887,1908]" captionTargetBox="[183,1374,1343,1825]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,1336,1865]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 7. Male genitalia. 5. Platychasma elegantula sp. nov. Holotype, Mao’ershan, Guangxi, China, 21 July 2007, leg. L. Chen; 6. Platychasma virgo Butler, Honshu, Japan, 1 May 1986, leg. K. Umetsu (Genitalia slide, SS- 5837, in National Science Museum, Tokyo, Japan); 7. Cyphanta xanthochlora Walker, Yunnan, China, 21 July 2006, leg. M. Wang and X. Fan." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/274412/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">
Figs. 
<number box="[641,684,1938,1961]" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" value="5.6">5, 6</number>
</figureCitation>
), but differ as follows: the apex of the valva is smooth; the gnathos is smaller, short and crook-shaped, and about half the length of the uncus; the aedeagus is stout, with thorn-like processes apically.
</paragraph>
